The select instruction visitor plays three roles specified by the mode.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="ac08c877d41b736633cb508edd2ae970aaa95eb9f0b68bdf443d603d529a3f9c74" />
<EnumerationListItem name="VM_counting">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ac08c877d41b736633cb508edd2ae970aaffb32b62adf3065e796714676d015f10" />
<EnumerationListItem name="VM_instrument">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ac08c877d41b736633cb508edd2ae970aa9460c859e26698ee1b200da54c0da797" />
<EnumerationListItem name="VM_annotate">

</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

In <code>VM&#95;counting</code> mode, it simply counts the number of select instructions. In <code>VM&#95;instrument</code> mode, it inserts code to count the number times TrueValue of select is taken. In <code>VM&#95;annotate</code> mode, it reads the profile data and annotate the select instruction with metadata.
